IMPORTANT LAPTOP PICK-UP SCHEDULE CHANGE:

To alleviate traffic issues on 5 Mile Line Road:

If you requested a laptop in the parent survey sent in early August and haven‚Äôt picked it up yet, you can do so tomorrow at the PHS North Entrance based on the following schedule:

10am - 12pm: PHS students

10am - 11am: Cobbles students

11am - 12pm: Harris Hill students

12pm - 1pm: Indian Landing students

1pm - 2pm: Scribner students

If you came to pick up a laptop on Tuesday and we did not have one for you, please do not come on Wednesday. We will configure a laptop for you after Wednesday and will be in touch.

Thank you for understanding.

Congratulations to our 2020 Fredenburg Award Winners: Lawrence Edson, East Greenbush Central School District, and Mark Sansouci, Penfield Central School District! This prestigious honor is awarded to individuals whose service and contributions over their long career had a positive impact on the Association, its members, and the entire profession.

Thank you to our Fredenburg Award Sponsor NYLAF!

post_text:
The following are results from the June 9, 2020 Penfield Central School District Budget Vote and Election, which was canvassed on June 16, 2020 and announced by Chairperson of Election Megan Dorritie, Esq.

Proposition #1: 2020-2021 Budget, passed Yes: 3840 No: 1299

Proposition #2:
Bus Purchases, passed Yes: 3900 No: 1232

BOE Candidates:
Dennis Bell 943 votes
Lisa Benati-Chidsey 2880 votes
Calvin Frelier 623 votes
Shaun Hakiel 1578 votes
Jason Hanna 925 votes
Shaun Pecora 496 votes
Gary Platek 1421 votes

Lisa Benati-Chidsey was elected to a three-year term commencing on July 1, 2020 to June 30, 2023.

Shaun Hakiel was elected to a three-year term commencing on July 1, 2020 to June 30, 2023.
